<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01 · Grease accumulation diagnostic</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Concentrated fuel in the path your kitchen uses every day.</h2>

    <p>Grease accumulation in commercial kitchen ventilation is the highest-stakes recurring service in the entire commercial appliance category. The grease that should be exhausted out the rooftop fan instead deposits on every surface along the exhaust path: hood plenum interior, baffle filter mesh, exhaust ductwork runs, fan housing, and rooftop fan unit itself.</p>

    <p>Why this matters operationally:</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Fire risk.</strong> Class K kitchen fires from grease are responsible for the majority of commercial restaurant fires nationally. A flare-up at the cooking surface can ignite duct grease, creating a fire that extends through the building.</li>
      <li><strong>NFPA 96 compliance.</strong> The standard sets cleaning cadence by cooking volume; missing schedule is a Fire Marshal violation flagged at routine inspection.</li>
      <li><strong>Health Department visibility.</strong> Grease-laden hoods and ductwork photograph poorly during food-service inspection; LADPH and OC Health Care Agency note ventilation condition.</li>
      <li><strong>Operational efficiency.</strong> Grease in the exhaust path increases static pressure drop, forcing the fan to work harder, accelerating motor wear, and reducing capture velocity at the hood face (smoke and steam stay in the kitchen instead of exhausting).</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with cleaning service.</strong> BHGS Licensed #A49573, EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410), C-20 HVAC scope. 90-day warranty. Sister sub-services: <a href="/commercial/exhaust-hood-repair/fan-not-working/">fan not working</a>, <a href="/commercial/exhaust-hood-repair/fire-suppression-issues/">fire suppression issues</a>, <a href="/commercial/exhaust-hood-repair/make-up-air-system-repair/">make-up air system</a>, <a href="/commercial/exhaust-hood-repair/hood-cleaning-service/">hood cleaning service</a>. Parent: <a href="/commercial/exhaust-hood-repair/">commercial exhaust hood repair pillar</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 NFPA 96 CADENCE -->
<section class="section section-gray">
